- Cones reworked to the reach-limit approach, dropping the destination-out clip entirely. Each of the three cones an exterior point throws now has reach = |q - centre| - rIn, i.e. it stops exactly at the annulus' inner boundary, so an exterior light's cast never enters the ring or the bowl (clip no longer needed; only interior points light inside). The three: WIDE tangent to the outer boundary (subtle base), MIDDLE tangent to the inner boundary (main glow), NARROW near-white flashlight (30% of the outer aperture); all share the apex at the point with the gradient brightest there, fading out by the inner boundary. Also calms the cast over the page content, as the lit area is much smaller now.

